I was just looking
at a friend of mine.

27:49.570 --> 27:54.174
Are you telling me
that I look like
a friend of yours?

27:54.207 --> 27:57.043
Hey, Kim, I think
he likes you.
(SCOFFS)

27:58.344 --> 27:59.780
Is that true?

27:59.813 --> 28:01.447
Do you like me?

28:02.583 --> 28:04.918
Do you love me?

28:06.887 --> 28:09.690
Uh, I like you
like a friend.

28:09.723 --> 28:11.792
I don't think so.

28:11.825 --> 28:14.094
I think you like me
like me.

28:15.395 --> 28:18.364
I think you want
to kiss me.

28:18.398 --> 28:19.833
Do you want to kiss me?

28:19.866 --> 28:21.101
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

28:21.902 --> 28:23.203
Uh, I don't know.

28:23.670 --> 28:25.405
Come on.

28:25.438 --> 28:28.308
Just one little kiss.

28:28.909 --> 28:30.777
I'll be your girlfriend.

28:37.250 --> 28:38.384
(CHUCKLES)
(SLAMS)

28:38.418 --> 28:39.886
In your dreams, geek.

28:44.024 --> 28:46.893
Maybe we should get her
to beat up Alan.

28:50.664 --> 28:52.899
Come on. Go.

28:53.499 --> 28:55.068
Go.

28:56.770 --> 28:57.804
(CHUCKLES)

28:57.838 --> 28:59.506
Wait for me, man.

29:03.577 --> 29:05.779
Be prepared to have
your mind blown.

29:11.718 --> 29:13.854
Check it out, man.

29:13.887 --> 29:16.923
That's, uh, 14 mounted toms,

29:16.957 --> 29:20.594
eight floor toms,
four splashes, two gongs,

29:20.627 --> 29:24.831
uh, ten cowbells,
four rides,
five snares, man...

29:24.865 --> 29:27.400
A roto‐tom rack,
and it's all mounted

29:27.433 --> 29:30.604
on my infamous
quadruple kick
drum system.

29:30.637 --> 29:34.307
Six more pieces,
I've got a bigger kit
than Neal Peart from Rush.

29:34.340 --> 29:35.509
Yeah!

29:35.542 --> 29:38.545
(CONFUSED)
That's great, Nick.

29:38.579 --> 29:43.116
Look, these teachers...
These teachers want us
to work, ya know?

29:43.149 --> 29:45.752
And I say,
"Fine. I'll work,

29:45.786 --> 29:49.455
"but you've gotta let me do
the kind of work
that I wanna do."

29:49.489 --> 29:51.457
And for me,
Lindsay, it's...

29:51.491 --> 29:53.827
It's my drum kit, man.

29:53.860 --> 29:55.161
This is my passion, ya know?

29:55.195 --> 29:59.165
This is...
This is the essence
of who I am now.

29:59.199 --> 30:02.736
But before I had this,
I was lost, too.

30:02.769 --> 30:04.304
You see what I'm sayin'?

30:04.337 --> 30:09.910
You need to find your reason
for, for living. I mean...

30:09.943 --> 30:14.147
You gotta find your big,
gigantic drum kit, ya know?

30:17.283 --> 30:18.752
(CHUCKLES)

30:18.785 --> 30:20.921
Hey, maybe
I'll buy a clarinet.

30:23.256 --> 30:24.725
Yeah.

30:24.758 --> 30:26.226
(CHUCKLES)

30:27.127 --> 30:28.261
If you're not
going to the dance,

30:28.294 --> 30:30.463
I thought you could
come over to my house.

30:30.496 --> 30:32.733
A bunch of guys
who play a guitar
are gonna come over.

30:32.766 --> 30:34.267
We're just, uh...
I don't know.

30:34.300 --> 30:36.870
We're gonna try playing
Dark Side of the Moon
or somethin'.

30:36.903 --> 30:38.872
Just tell your dad
you went.

30:38.905 --> 30:41.608
I can't lie to my dad.

30:42.275 --> 30:43.276
Really?

30:45.145 --> 30:47.080
Yeah.

30:47.113 --> 30:48.481
Okay.

30:48.515 --> 30:51.451
Why don't you
tell your dad
that you got a date?

30:51.484 --> 30:52.719
No. Listen...

30:52.753 --> 30:55.388
I'll put on
a suit, all right?

30:55.421 --> 30:56.990
I'll come pick you up,

30:57.023 --> 30:58.058
talk nice to your dad,

30:58.091 --> 30:59.259
and then I'll take you
to the school,

30:59.292 --> 31:01.928
and we can walk up to
the door of the dance,

31:01.962 --> 31:04.230
and then we can take off.

31:04.264 --> 31:06.900
That way you can tell
your dad you went.
You wouldn't be lyin'.

31:08.434 --> 31:09.469
You'd really do that?

31:11.337 --> 31:12.539
Absolutely.

31:12.573 --> 31:13.974
(CAR HORN HONKS)

31:14.675 --> 31:16.176
(CLEARS THROAT)

31:19.946 --> 31:21.147
Hello there!

31:21.815 --> 31:23.449
Hello, Jeff.

31:23.483 --> 31:25.118
Guess who's in trouble?

31:27.754 --> 31:30.090
Here's the deal:

31:30.123 --> 31:32.826
If you take part in
the Academic Decathlon,

31:32.859 --> 31:35.061
I'll forget this
ever happened.

31:36.262 --> 31:38.498
You're forcing me
to be a math‐lete?

31:39.499 --> 31:40.767
That is so not fair.

31:40.801 --> 31:43.436
(CHUCKLES) The world
is not black and white.

31:43.469 --> 31:44.838
It's gray.

31:44.871 --> 31:47.340
And I really think
it'd be good for you.

31:47.373 --> 31:48.474
Jeff...

31:49.242 --> 31:51.244
I really
can't do that.

31:54.314 --> 31:56.382
Fine, Ms. Weir.

31:56.416 --> 31:59.185
Then maybe it's time
for some tough love.

31:59.219 --> 32:01.421
How about I, uh,
call your parents,

32:01.454 --> 32:03.189
and I let them know
that their daughter's

32:03.223 --> 32:06.326
turning into a burnout
who skips class?
No.

32:06.359 --> 32:07.728
And you know what?

32:07.761 --> 32:10.496
I can't make you
be a math‐lete,

32:10.531 --> 32:13.834
but I can make you work
the refreshment table

32:13.867 --> 32:16.169
at the homecoming dance.

32:16.202 --> 32:19.005
(SCOFFS)
I'll see ya Saturday
at 7:00.

32:19.906 --> 32:21.542
HAROLD: You know
who used to cut class?

32:21.975 --> 32:23.777
Jimi Hendrix.

32:23.810 --> 32:25.111
You know what happened to him?

32:25.145 --> 32:28.448
He died, choking
on his own vomit.

32:28.481 --> 32:31.084
Daddy,
I skipped Latin.

32:31.117 --> 32:32.185
Oh, well,
I can understand

32:32.218 --> 32:34.387
why you wouldn't want
to learn about that.

32:34.420 --> 32:37.423
It's only
the building block
of our language.

32:37.457 --> 32:40.627
Well, I'm just glad
your grandmother
wasn't alive

32:40.661 --> 32:42.328
to hear about this.

32:43.864 --> 32:46.633
You can't cut corners
in life!

32:46.667 --> 32:48.735
You know who cut corners?
Kennedy.

32:48.769 --> 32:51.772
Kennedy cut corners
when he was running
the bay of pigs.

32:51.805 --> 32:54.708
A lot of good men
lost their lives
because of it.

32:55.676 --> 32:56.977
You know who else cut corners?

32:57.010 --> 32:58.244
Janis Joplin.

32:58.278 --> 32:59.880
Dad!

32:59.913 --> 33:02.115
What are you talking about?

33:02.148 --> 33:03.650
You don't make any sense!

33:03.684 --> 33:07.053
I just cut class,
and, guess what?
Everybody's still alive.

33:07.087 --> 33:09.189
Just leave me alone!

33:12.092 --> 33:13.527
(DOOR SLAMS)

33:16.763 --> 33:18.532
You understand
what I'm saying,
don't ya, Sam?

33:21.535 --> 33:23.637
Y‐yeah.
Good.

33:23.670 --> 33:24.738
Pass the rolls.

33:35.616 --> 33:36.683
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

33:36.717 --> 33:38.084
(DOOR OPENS)

33:40.353 --> 33:42.589
Um, do you want me
to come... Can I come in?

33:49.830 --> 33:53.800
Do you think that
me, Neal, and Bill
could beat up Alan?

33:57.337 --> 33:58.371
Just Alan?

33:59.906 --> 34:01.642
Yeah.

34:01.675 --> 34:03.644
Alan and his buddies?

34:03.677 --> 34:05.211
Hmm... No to maybe.

34:06.079 --> 34:07.781
Yeah.
That's what I thought.

34:11.251 --> 34:14.555
Um, why are you
throwing your life away?

34:16.523 --> 34:18.759
Did Dad tell you
to ask me that?

34:19.893 --> 34:21.928
No. Millie did.

34:21.962 --> 34:24.297
(SCOFFS) That figures.

34:25.498 --> 34:26.466
Forget it.

34:26.499 --> 34:29.202
You know, tell her
to mind her own business.

34:32.472 --> 34:35.041
You know, just because
she asked me to ask you

34:35.075 --> 34:37.511
doesn't mean I was gonna
tell her what you said.

34:41.515 --> 34:42.583
Sam?

34:45.485 --> 34:46.720
Did Mom and Dad
ever tell you

34:46.753 --> 34:48.855
that I was the only one
with Grandma
when she died?

34:50.557 --> 34:51.658
No.

34:53.459 --> 34:55.796
Yeah.

34:55.829 --> 34:59.432
They went down
to the cafeteria
to get some coffee,

35:00.767 --> 35:03.537
and all of a sudden,
Grandma looked so
terrified.

35:04.237 --> 35:06.439
I didn't know
what to do.

35:07.473 --> 35:08.675
(SIGHS)

35:08.709 --> 35:13.246
She grabbed my hand
and told me she
didn't want to go.

35:13.279 --> 35:15.582
She looked
so scared, Sam.

35:17.017 --> 35:18.351
So, I said,
"Well, you know,

35:18.384 --> 35:24.190
"can you see God
or heaven or a light
or anything?"

35:24.224 --> 35:25.826
What did she say?

35:27.327 --> 35:28.494
"No.

35:29.996 --> 35:31.364
"There's nothing."

35:34.100 --> 35:36.803
She was a good person
all her life,
and that's what she got.

35:46.680 --> 35:47.748
So...

35:48.649 --> 35:50.851
You do think that
we could beat up Alan?

35:59.492 --> 36:00.527
Yeah.

36:01.928 --> 36:03.196
He's a goner.

36:10.671 --> 36:12.338
(DOOR CLOSES)

36:12.372 --> 36:16.009
<i>♪♪ Oh, Mama,</i>
<i>I'm in fear for my life</i>

36:16.042 --> 36:21.515
<i>♪♪ From the long arm</i>
<i>of the law</i>

36:22.749 --> 36:26.987
<i>♪♪ Lawman has put an end</i>
<i>to my runnin'</i>

36:27.020 --> 36:32.225
<i>♪♪ And I'm so far</i>
<i>from my home</i>

36:33.359 --> 36:37.297
<i>♪♪ Oh, Mama,</i>
<i>I can hear you a‐cryin'</i>

36:37.330 --> 36:38.765
<i>♪♪ You're so scared... ♪♪</i>

36:38.799 --> 36:40.534
Oh, man, where's Sam?

36:40.567 --> 36:42.468
It's almost 3 o'clock.
Alan's gonna be here.

36:42.503 --> 36:45.506
I'll bet
he forgot his math book.
I'm sure he's coming.

36:45.539 --> 36:46.873
All right.

36:47.508 --> 36:48.341
Colin!

36:48.374 --> 36:49.409
You came
to help us?

36:49.442 --> 36:51.244
No way.
I just came
to watch.

36:51.277 --> 36:52.846
It should be
exciting.

36:52.879 --> 36:55.916
Uh, because
we're gonna win?

36:55.949 --> 36:57.450
Either way.

36:58.118 --> 36:59.853
Oh, man,
where's Sam?

37:01.287 --> 37:02.723
Sam.
I can't talk.

37:02.756 --> 37:03.757
Gotta fight Alan.

37:07.894 --> 37:09.329
Hi, Sam.

37:12.265 --> 37:14.400
Oh, hi, Cindy.

37:14.434 --> 37:16.937
(SCOFFS) Where's Sam?
It's 3 o'clock.

37:17.604 --> 37:18.805
Oh, okay.

37:18.839 --> 37:20.874
So now don't let Alan
hit any of your
pressure points

37:20.907 --> 37:23.343
because if he does,
you're not gonna
feel anything,

37:23.376 --> 37:24.878
but you'll drop dead
in three days.

37:27.480 --> 37:29.115
Oh, man,
my stomach hurts.

37:29.149 --> 37:30.851
Bill, you'll be fine.

37:30.884 --> 37:32.418
No, it really hurts.

37:32.452 --> 37:34.087
I think
I should go home.

37:34.120 --> 37:36.389
This is how
Houdini died.

37:36.422 --> 37:38.525
Oh, you should
always guard
your face

37:38.559 --> 37:39.893
because if the other guy
hits you in the nose,

37:39.926 --> 37:41.595
it could drive
the nose bone
into your brain,

37:41.628 --> 37:44.297
and then you'll release
your bowels and die.

37:44.330 --> 37:46.432
Shut up, would ya?
No. He's right.

37:46.466 --> 37:49.670
There are
a lot of ways
to die in a fight.

37:49.703 --> 37:51.972
(SIGHS) Maybe we
should put this off.

37:52.005 --> 37:53.774
Hey, there's Sam.

37:53.807 --> 37:55.175
Sam!

37:55.208 --> 37:57.043
Sam!

37:57.077 --> 37:58.512
Sam!
Stop it.
Stop it, you moron.

37:58.545 --> 38:00.681
That's not Sam.
It's Alan.

38:00.714 --> 38:01.715
What?

38:02.415 --> 38:04.450
So, um,
what are you doin'?

38:04.484 --> 38:06.419
Just goin' home.
How about you?

38:06.452 --> 38:08.822
(CHUCKLES)
I'm cheering
at the game.

38:09.389 --> 38:10.857
Oh. (CHUCKLES)

38:10.891 --> 38:14.427
Well... you're dressed
for it. (CHUCKLES)

38:16.496 --> 38:19.232
What are you losers
doin' on my street?
Nothing.

38:19.265 --> 38:20.801
We're kind of here
to beat you up.

38:20.834 --> 38:22.636
Bill!
Well, we are.

38:22.669 --> 38:23.604
Are you?

38:23.637 --> 38:24.971
He's... He's just...
He's kidding.

38:25.005 --> 38:27.207
I'm not talkin'
to you, dork!
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

38:27.240 --> 38:28.274
(IMITATES CHUCKLING)

38:28.308 --> 38:29.475
What are you
laughin' at, pinhead?

38:29.510 --> 38:32.278
Oh, I'm just here
to watch.
Oh, really?

38:32.312 --> 38:33.580
Well, watch this.

38:33.614 --> 38:35.015
(GRUNTING)

38:39.686 --> 38:41.221
(SCREAMS)

38:41.254 --> 38:44.090
(GRUNTING CONTINUES)

38:48.228 --> 38:49.763
You are so dead.

38:49.796 --> 38:50.831
(GROANS)

38:51.732 --> 38:52.799
(SCREAMS)

38:55.268 --> 38:56.369
GIRL: Come on.

38:56.402 --> 38:58.138
I gotta get out there.

38:58.171 --> 39:00.707
I'll see ya.
All right. See ya.

39:02.308 --> 39:03.944
Hey, Cindy?

39:03.977 --> 39:05.011
Yeah?

39:07.480 --> 39:09.616
I was wondering, um...

39:12.786 --> 39:14.387
Do, uh...

39:15.188 --> 39:17.390
(GRUNTING)

39:18.859 --> 39:20.460
(GROANS)

39:20.493 --> 39:22.362
You wanna piece of me?
I'll kill you!

39:22.395 --> 39:23.429
ALAN: Bring it on.

39:23.463 --> 39:24.865
(BOTH GRUNTING)

39:27.968 --> 39:29.102
Um...

39:32.438 --> 39:34.641
Do you wanna go to
the Homecoming Dance
with me?

39:35.809 --> 39:37.644
Well, I'm already going
with Dan Lewis.

39:37.678 --> 39:39.613
He asked me two weeks ago.

39:42.616 --> 39:45.251
Oh, okay.
I mean... Yeah.

39:45.285 --> 39:46.853
I just thought
I would ask

39:46.887 --> 39:48.989
just in case you
didn't have anyone
to go with.

39:50.490 --> 39:51.692
Well, um...

39:51.725 --> 39:54.060
I gotta get out there,
so I'll see ya.

39:54.094 --> 39:57.598
Oh, if you're there,
I'll save a dance
for you.

39:58.832 --> 40:00.033
Okay.

40:01.668 --> 40:02.836
See ya.

40:05.138 --> 40:06.573
That could be good.

40:08.408 --> 40:09.610
(SIGHS)

40:10.276 --> 40:12.212
(GRUNTING)

40:12.245 --> 40:14.715
Get off me,
you psychos!

40:17.984 --> 40:19.586
You ripped my shirt.

40:19.620 --> 40:21.454
You're gonna buy me
a new shirt!

40:21.487 --> 40:23.690
You guys
are all dead, man!
Really dead!

40:28.762 --> 40:30.496
I got punched
in the nose, but,

40:30.531 --> 40:32.365
but I'm still alive.

40:32.398 --> 40:34.968
I guess my nose bone
must have missed
my brain.

40:35.001 --> 40:37.504
Yeah. My stomach
doesn't hurt anymore.

40:38.171 --> 40:39.272
Mine does.

40:39.305 --> 40:41.241
(GROANS)

40:41.274 --> 40:43.510
Did you see me?
I was taunting him.

40:43.544 --> 40:45.746
He was terrified.

40:45.779 --> 40:50.016
Did you see me?
I had his arms.
Totally shut him down.

40:50.050 --> 40:51.652
I had his shoes.

40:54.788 --> 40:55.989
Wait a minute.

40:56.690 --> 40:59.125
You... You guys fought Alan?

40:59.159 --> 41:01.227
No.
We got hit by a car.

41:01.261 --> 41:03.429
SAM: Listen,
I'm so sorry.

41:03.463 --> 41:05.165
I was talkin' to Cindy.

41:06.466 --> 41:07.868
You really stood up for me.

41:07.901 --> 41:09.703
You should see
how he looks.

41:09.736 --> 41:12.072
We tore his shirt.
Yeah.

41:12.105 --> 41:13.406
So what'd she say?

41:13.439 --> 41:15.108
She's got a date.

41:15.141 --> 41:17.043
She's saving
a dance for me.

41:17.077 --> 41:18.211
So you're goin'.

41:19.012 --> 41:20.180
Yeah.

41:20.213 --> 41:22.616
You've gotta
slow dance.

41:22.649 --> 41:24.885
Yeah.
Definitely slow.

41:25.919 --> 41:28.789
Thanks. You know,
I'll be there
the next time.

41:28.822 --> 41:31.725
Oh, God,
I hope there's
not a next time.

41:31.758 --> 41:34.995
( COME SAIL AWAY PLAYING)

41:41.167 --> 41:47.574
<i>♪♪ I'm sailing away</i>

41:50.243 --> 41:52.813
<i>♪♪ Set an open course</i>

41:52.846 --> 41:54.881
<i>♪♪ For the virgin sea...</i>

41:54.915 --> 41:57.584
Look, uh, I know
you're not happy
about this,

41:57.618 --> 42:00.020
but don't make me
the bad guy here.

42:00.053 --> 42:01.922
<i>♪♪ Got to be free...</i>

42:01.955 --> 42:03.056
If the worst thing
in your life

42:03.089 --> 42:04.658
is somebody makes you
go to a dance,

42:04.691 --> 42:08.161
then I'd say
you have a pretty
good life.

42:09.129 --> 42:14.200
<i>♪♪ That's ahead of me</i>

42:14.234 --> 42:18.104
<i>♪♪ On board, I'm a captain</i>

42:18.138 --> 42:22.208
<i>♪♪ So climb aboard</i>

42:22.242 --> 42:26.246
<i>♪♪ We'll search for tomorrow</i>

42:26.279 --> 42:29.015
<i>♪♪ On every shore</i>

42:29.049 --> 42:31.484
<i>♪♪ And I'll try</i>

42:31.518 --> 42:36.189
<i>♪♪ Oh, Lord, I'll try</i>

42:38.291 --> 42:45.265
<i>♪♪ To carry on...</i>

42:48.969 --> 42:50.336
(INAUDIBLE)

42:52.338 --> 42:53.740
(SIGHS)

42:53.774 --> 42:59.946
<i>♪♪ I look to the sea...</i>

42:59.980 --> 43:00.981
Hi, Cindy.

43:01.515 --> 43:02.883
Hey, Sam.

43:04.484 --> 43:06.720
I was wondering, um...

43:07.788 --> 43:10.056
You said you'd save
that dance for me,

43:10.090 --> 43:12.225
so can I have it now?

43:12.258 --> 43:15.562
<i>♪♪ Some happy, some sad...</i>

43:15.596 --> 43:17.263
I mean,
if you're not busy?

43:19.099 --> 43:20.133
I'm not busy.

43:20.166 --> 43:21.768
<i>♪♪ Of childhood friends</i>

43:21.802 --> 43:25.205
<i>♪♪ And the dreams we had</i>

43:26.873 --> 43:31.111
<i>♪♪ We lived happily forever</i>

43:31.144 --> 43:34.981
<i>♪♪ So the story goes</i>

43:35.015 --> 43:38.885
<i>♪♪ But somehow we missed out</i>

43:38.919 --> 43:41.622
<i>♪♪ On the pot of gold</i>

43:41.655 --> 43:44.224
<i>♪♪ But we'll try</i>

43:44.257 --> 43:49.162
<i>♪♪ Best as we can</i>

43:50.731 --> 43:55.268
<i>♪♪ To carry on...</i>

44:00.106 --> 44:01.207
Come on, Sam.

44:07.681 --> 44:10.851
<i>♪♪ A gathering of angels</i>

44:10.884 --> 44:14.087
<i>♪♪ Appeared above my head</i>

44:14.120 --> 44:17.591
<i>♪♪ They sang to me</i>
<i>this song of hope</i>

44:17.624 --> 44:19.960
